This simulator is just a practice of JSON-SERVER module. 
This package will simulate a backend, getting data from db.json
There are three tables in db.json file called students, subjects and enrollments.


1. Pre-requirements: 
a) create a node project typing the command line in a choosen folder "npm init -y"
b) install globally the package json-server typing the command line "npm install -g json-server"


2. Start the aplication typing:
start the application typing "json-server --watch db.json"

The application will start on localhost:3000. Try that URL on your browser


3. Running simulator in a specific port:
You can choose de port where simulator serve data typing --PORT and number as following.
   "json-server --watch db.json --port 3004"

4. Based on our db.json, you can try following routes. The simulator can simulate CRUD operations:
GET    http://localhost:3000/students
GET    http://localhost:3000/students/1
POST   http://localhost:3000/students
PUT    http://localhost:3000/students/1
PATCH  http://localhost:3000/students/1
DELETE http://localhost:3000/students/1

5. You can get more information about package, routes and others at 
https://www.npmjs.com/package/json-server#alternative-port